10001.Name: Stone
10001.Description: The Quarrel Shooter uses it sometimes.

10005.Name: Vubbe Extermination Bomb
10005.Description: It seems the name is unique, but the effect is similar to another bomb.

10007.Name: Bomb_Defence
10007.Description: It has a same meaning as the name. There is no special thing.

11110.Name: New_desmodus
11110.Description: A popular theory is that you have to be a demon to use this messenger.

11119.Name: Treasure Vubbe
11119.Description: They are surely Vubbes, but they live another life.

11123.Name: Goblin_Spear_red
11123.Description: Over time these Vubbes have become diverse and distinguishable.

11125.Name: Goblin_Miners
11125.Description: It is hard to determine whether their mining roles are permanent since little is known about the Vubbe's social system.

11160.Name: Goblin_Archer
11160.Description: Vubbe Archers specialize in using ranged weapons. Thus some people claim Vubbes have specific roles.

11162.Name: Goblin_Archer_red
11162.Description: It is possible to collect and use the bows and arrows that the Vubbes made.

11310.Name: Eye of Mirtis
11310.Description: Demon Lord Mirtis said the man was his servant. Some say it was a clone of her...

41196.Name: Long_Arm
41196.Description: A shrub monster that attacks by either firing its twigs or striking with its branches.

41197.Name: Rocktor
41197.Description: This monster belongs to the group of the Infro Rocktor.

41198.Name: dog_of_king
41198.Description: According to legend this watchdog is a creation that Zachariel the Great had planned to preserve.

41201.Name: boss_onion_the_great
41201.Description: The research to find out why some Kepas transformed to like this is progressing. Even the research to see if it was edible, but still, nothing is certain.

41202.Name: Poata
41202.Description: Poata is trying to find chances to showoff to the demons to obtain more power from the monsters originated plants.

41203.Name: Deadborn
41203.Description: A monster that returned from the dead, accurately saying it is a monster that resurrected into a demon after it died.

41205.Name: boss_salamander
41205.Description: A monster that already existed before Medzio Diena. It used to have a liking towards humans in the past, but that feeling has faded away in the current times.

41207.Name: Saltistter
41207.Description: Basically, It was born in the cold region, after Medzio Diena, it is actively working around because spotted in many areas.

41208.Name: boss_ginklas
41208.Description: Current Ginklas is caught by madness, so there is no chance to show his original rationality.

41209.Name: Stone Whale
41209.Description: It is not yet clear why Stone Whale has a form of Whale even it mutated from mininals.

41210.Name: Tutu
41210.Description: Since Medzio Diena, amphibians have became to various forms, so Tutu seems as same as the original form. Of course, it is ferocious.

41211.Name: Yonazolem
41211.Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.

41212.Name: Master Genie
41212.Description: Many fairy and spirits sided with the demons and not the humans and the goddesses. The rest of them are hidden and lurking. Genie is one of them.

41213.Name: Biteregina
41213.Description: Insect monsters mutated at Medzio Diena have some queen and master entity.

41214.Name: boss_Iltiswort
41214.Description: The advantage can be found the powerful monsters are that many of them can't move to another place.

41215.Name: boss_GiantWoodGoblin_red
41215.Description: The forest became horror after Medzio Diena. It mainly caused by the large scale monsters to be hard to defeat.

41216.Name: Lepus
41216.Description: In the past this animal was quite friendly towards humans, but now it's even more dangerous than demons.

41217.Name: boss_mushcaria
41217.Description: For reasons unknown, it was mutated after Medzio Diena and shown to be very hostile.

41219.Name: boss_chafer
41219.Description: It doesn't matter to humans, but they don't like other insect types, especially bee type monsters.

41220.Name: boss_Gaigalas
41220.Description: It is little ambiguous which types of lives become the source of Gaigalas. It is suspicious if they existed in our world.

41221.Name: boss_Throneweaver
41221.Description: Insect-types that possess the strong power either end up becoming a slaughterer or try to become influential. The latter is especially dangerous since they are holding hands with demons and the Throneweaver belongs in this category.

41222.Name: Bebraspion
41222.Description: In the past, there were a few attempts to tame humans in their childhood, but the demons were the ones who eventually succeeded.

41223.Name: Soggy Mushwort
41223.Description: What's most difficult for these kinds of monsters is that they may appear in houses...

41224.Name: boss_sparnas
41224.Description: It is a bird so it's only logical that bird seeds are tempting. The demons are trying to use this to their advantage and they induce them to harass humans.

41225.Name: Mineloader
41225.Description: It is unsure whether it turned into a monster after Medzio Diena or by receiving some ritual from a Demon Lord. No matter what, this equipment was useful back then.

41226.Name: Rajatoad
41226.Description: It is not known whether these monsters transformed after Medzio Diena and moved from the sea to the land as a result or they are originally demonic lives. Goddess Jurate is not interested in them.

41227.Name: boss_ShadowGaoler
41227.Description: Shadowgaler was originally one of the spirits, but it embraced the power of the demons on Medzio Diena.

41228.Name: Helgasercle
41228.Description: Helgasercle used to be one of the strongest Demon Lords out there. Hauberk who was also the Demon Lord who received her wrath and was sealed after she showed her powers. It is not strange that Agailla Flurry is praised by many as the greatest mage in history since she fought against Helgasercle for hundreds of years and won.

41229.Name: boss_lecifer
41229.Description: Rexipher is known as the wisest Demon Lord among all Demon Lords. The reason why he is not active as he should be is because the Demon Queen Gesti doesn't know how to use him effectively. That is good for humans.

41230.Name: boss_necrovanter
41230.Description: He has the tendency to control evil spirits and steal the power from those who do not obey him in order to accumulate even greater power.

41231.Name: Wriggling Lutopus
41231.Description: The reason why these kind of monsters are being created from the land and the lives that are not relevant to the sea is due to the demons. It sounds simple, but in fact this phenomenon cannot be explained that simple.

41232.Name: Linkroller
41232.Description: The theory how Link Roller moves by which magical reaction has been proven. However, what's interesting is that it is not designed by somene, but it was just created naturally around Medzio Diena.

41233.Name: boss_Rocktortuga
41233.Description: When Rocktortuga first appeared, many soldiers had difficulties retreating due to it's stubborness. As time went by, the weakness on its body was made known, but it's not easy to attack weakness of Rocktortuga.

41235.Name: Poisonous Rytaswort
41235.Description: Many people are participating on the efforts to prevent them from producing their offsprings by spurting out spores.

41236.Name: Ravinepede
41236.Description: It was never observed before that the monster which was originally a bug turned into an imago type monster. It shouldn't occur when you look at it.

41237.Name: Netherbovine
41237.Description: Nederbovine bases it's origin to the demon realm. This is not an intelligent demon. It is a beast that is being raised by the demons.

41238.Name: boss_Carnivore
41238.Description: We don't know which animal he consumed to obtain the eyes he has.

41239.Name: boss_TombLord
41239.Description: A long time ago, he was the hidden guardian who used to protect the grave from the robbers.

41244.Name: boss_Strongholder
41244.Description: The ones who were known as strong warriors in the demon realm stepped into our world because of Giltine's orders.

41245.Name: Archon
41245.Description: Archon belongs to a high class in the demon realm and he is responsible for many things besides the battles.

41246.Name: Carapace
41246.Description: Many monsters created lots of diverse transformations on Medzio Diena, but Carapace is unique among them. It was created from the shell which was molted from other animals.

41247.Name: Werewolf
41247.Description: Beowolfs have been drifting diverse worlds from a long time ago. They don't belong to any world and they think Medzio Diena will be a good chance for them.

41248.Name: Tiny
41248.Description: Due to their cute appearances, many people tried to tame Tinis, but they never succeeded.

41249.Name: TreeAmbulo
41249.Description: Tree Ambulo is different from the typical monsters that originated from the demon realm as it is not a deformity between creatures and things.

41250.Name: Golemlet
41250.Description: A small form of Golem that is harmful to humans because it receives evil influences.

41252.Name: Spion
41252.Description: It's well-trained to follow its owner's every command. Unfortunately, its owner is usually a demon.

41257.Name: Yekubite
41257.Description: Yekub unleashes its infamous cry in the demon realm, which produces many minions and spreads them around the world. Yekubite is the name given to these minions.

41258.Name: Shardstatue
41258.Description: A possessed demonic monster obsessed with the divine Goddess Statues.

41260.Name: Cire
41260.Description: This monster does not seem to transmute from typical plants but rather from rotten flora. However, there are no evidence to support this conclusion.

41264.Name: TreeGool
41264.Description: Upon transforming into a monster with a hardened wood body and no leaves, Treegool supplants its former photosynthetic diet with hunting.

41266.Name: Ammon
41266.Description: Ammon has been existing from the ancient times and killed many people.

41268.Name: Chafperor
41268.Description: A severely mutated bee and beetle hybrid with qualities of both, it operates in swarms.

41269.Name: RavineLerva
41269.Description: Before it was discovered that it was a transformation of a plant, there was speculation that it could be some monster's larva.

41273.Name: Vesper
41273.Description: Animals living in the Royal Mausoleum have been deformed in recent years by the influence of the evil energy.

41274.Name: Karas
41274.Description: It is a magic creature whose name comes from the wishes of a golem species.

41275.Name: Echad
41275.Description: A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the goddess' powers.

41276.Name: shtayim
41276.Description: Despite its appearance, this magical creation has received the blessing of the goddess. Can deal critical damage to demons.

41277.Name: Tombsinker
41277.Description: Many creatures have been placed in the Royal Mausoleum, including the Tombsinker, to guard against intruding demons.

41280.Name: Weaver
41280.Description: There are rumors saying the Weaver is looking for thread made of stone.

41285.Name: Meleech
41285.Description: Firm and toxic, their blood-sucking ability is unique.

41287.Name: Zolem
41287.Description: Unlike traditional Golems, Zolem move by a mysterious aura, not magic.

41288.Name: raider
41288.Description: Although a Kepa by name, it actually comes from the demon realm.

41290.Name: wood_goblin
41290.Description: An evil goblin summoned by the Vubbes. It sometimes appear even in areas where Vubbes are not found.

41294.Name: Woodin
41294.Description: You shouldn't misunderstand Woodin that doesn't move as a good stump.

41295.Name: StonOrca
41295.Description: A mutant monster that looks like a dolphin. Its other features correspond to a small Stone Whale.

41297.Name: Drape
41297.Description: Although a clyra type because of its sharp tail, this monster seems to have transformed from a pumpkin.

41298.Name: Infro Holder
41298.Description: The demons appearance caused many mutations. Infro Holders are one of them.

41299.Name: Lepusbunny
41299.Description: In the past this animal was quite friendly towards humans, but now it's even more dangerous than a bear.

41302.Name: Minos
41302.Description: According to a legend, Minos spent all its life by just fighting. This is because some Demon Lords used them as their servants to check on other Demon Lords.

41303.Name: Armory
41303.Description: The Armori are dullahans whose armors are stained by evil energy.

41306.Name: Hound
41306.Description: Is that another tail hanging on its back?

41307.Name: Stoulet
41307.Description: A demon that respects the strong and is cruel to the weak. Nonetheless, its aggression trivializes this characteristic.

41310.Name: InfroBurk
41310.Description: We don't know which monster's mini version Infroburks are. One thing for sure is that they are vicious.

41312.Name: Night Maiden
41312.Description: They are servants and body guards to the Demon Lords.

41313.Name: Worg
41313.Description: It is not sure whether worgs interact with human spirits or they are one of the wolf species from the ancient times.

41315.Name: Prison Fighter
41315.Description: They kill their fellow demons out of boredom.

41319.Name: InfroRocktor
41319.Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.

41322.Name: Maggot
41322.Description: People used to think that they were influenced on Medzio Diena, but they grew up.

41348.Name: Cactusvel
41348.Description: This monster appears in the regions of the kingdom where the climate is not adequate for cacti.

41349.Name: boss_Kimeleech
41349.Description: Kirmeleech sucks the blood of either monsters or demons since humans are too small to them. However, they do attack humans, so it's actually not important whether they suck blood from humans or not.

41350.Name: Magburk
41350.Description: Even the demons who caused Medzio Diena don't know whether Magburks around them would turn out like that.

41351.Name: boss_Naktis
41351.Description: Naktis has three sisters who are Demon Lords and they are all related to the Demon Queen Gesti.

41352.Name: boss_Drapeliun
41352.Description: Most Plant-type monsters used to be threatening to small animals, but they became bigger after Medzio Diena and became threatening to humans as well.

41353.Name: Sparnashorn
41353.Description: Some people are not giving up and are trying to tame bird monsters. If they succeed, they would help a lot in battles and transportations.

41354.Name: boss_Ironbaum
41354.Description: There's a rumor going around that Ironbaum used to be the target of practice for the demons. Regardless of what their origin is, they are threats to us now.

41362.Name: bubbe_chaser
41362.Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated.

41367.Name: Glass Mole
41367.Description: There's a rumor that the monster who broke into the Royal Mausoleum which Demon Lord Rexipher modified is the starting point.

41368.Name: boss_Denoptic
41368.Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Vaiga uses. Vaiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.

41369.Name: boss_Sparnanman
41369.Description: Although its name is similar, it is not related to the monsters that turned out from the birds.

41370.Name: Tomb Maiden
41370.Description: The Great King Zachariel destroyed the majority of his documents since he was worried about any intrusion. Therefore, we don't know if Tomb Maiden was created by humans.

41371.Name: Unknocker
41371.Description: It is the creation of magic that mages and humans frequently used to protect their treasures.

41372.Name: Mummyghast
41372.Description: In theory, this monster's creation is similar to Dullahan. However, the combined object is not a shield.

41373.Name: Kubas
41373.Description: Rexipher tried many times to infiltrate into the royal tomb. He didn't succeed the infiltration, but he was able to make a monster called Kubas.

41374.Name: Grinender
41374.Description: This info might not be useful to you in real battles, but this monster is very weak against other demons.

41375.Name: Pyroego
41375.Description: It is such a pity that many spirits held hands with the strong spirits since Medzio Diena. There are opinions that strategic negotiations should take place from now on.

41376.Name: boss_Gorgon
41376.Description: The demons are controlling the strong ones among the creatures that turned into monsters on Medzio Diena. Gorgon used to exist even before Medzio Diena, but it's form and the habit is different from the past.

41377.Name: Lithorex
41377.Description: This arrogant monster betrayed the blessing of the goddess is a shame to the goddesses.

41378.Name: boss_moa
41378.Description: Among the ones who try to tame many different kinds of birds, many of them are not interested in Moas. Because this bird eats too much.

41379.Name: Scorpio
41379.Description: Although its name is not unique, this monster in fact will is the most faithful companion of death that you will encounter.

41380.Name: boss_Deathweaver
41380.Description: The history of Deathweaver became known to humans has been very long and many warriors and mages died in the net that were created by the monsters.

41381.Name: boss_Templeshooter
41381.Description: The most dramatic change the Goblin society experienced on Medzio Diena is the appearances of the strong individuals like the Temple Shooter. However, they prioritize their individual benefits more than the Goblin tribe. Even if they serve for others, there's a certain possibility that they have hidden purposes.

41382.Name: boss_Chapparition
41382.Description: It is known that Chapparitions were being created when the spirits of dead mages fell into evil deeds.

41383.Name: boss_Minotaurs
41383.Description: Minotaurs used to exist from a long time ago and besides from the fact that one other species with wings came out from it, they are violent as usual.

41384.Name: Cerberus
41384.Description: Compared to the goddesses, the demons either grow or create demons that protect their territories. According to a legend, Cerberus didn't have the form it now has.

41385.Name: Cursed Devilglove
41385.Description: Legend has it that this is an object of the ancient devil whose identity is unknown. According to that legend, even Giltine didn't want to fight against it.

41409.Name: Crystal Spider
41409.Description: Because of its appearance, novice miners often try to mine the crystal on the spider's back and are attacked.

41413.Name: Filibo
41413.Description: Those who see Filibo as a small and cute critter will quickly be injured by it.

41418.Name: Bat
41418.Description: Acting as Mirtis' scout minion, these bats once lived throughout the world but have grown into a large threat despite of their small bodies.

41433.Name: hogma_warrior
41433.Description: Hogma is smarter than the Vubbes so they use tools, but due to its strong instinct, it tends to make mistakes and hardly makes any progress.

41434.Name: hogma_archer
41434.Description: Levelheaded Hogmas are often seen taking the role of archers.

41435.Name: hogma_sorcerer
41435.Description: Among the Hogmas, there is someone who obtained the abilities through experiences. But, a sorcerer is not free from the instinct of a Hogma.

41436.Name: Ellom
41436.Description: It is said that they receive their powers from human souls because they gather toward the injured.

41437.Name: Green Ellom
41437.Description: This type of Ellom is toxic.

41439.Name: merog_wizzard
41439.Description: Merog variant. Slight differences in the mutation process differentiates the variety of Merogs.

41440.Name: Merog Stinger
41440.Description: This reptile monster attacks instinctively but shows as much abilities as its intelligence.

41441.Name: warleader_hogma
41441.Description: A Hogma whose intelligence and instinct give them leadership in the fight against humans.

41442.Name: chupaluka
41442.Description: A monster which is said to be created by demons using the Chupacabra.

41443.Name: Ellomago
41443.Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.

41444.Name: ellogua
41444.Description: It is fierce against other monsters and humans, more so especially with insect type monsters.

41445.Name: groll
41445.Description: Amphibians that have branched out and evolved to be able to hunt in arid areas, travelers should be wary of them.

41446.Name: wendigo
41446.Description: A monster with a habit of baiting and attacking humans.

41447.Name: Lizardman
41447.Description: It is a Beast-type monster whose origin can be easily identified from its appearance and its name.

41448.Name: Tama
41448.Description: Tama is a monster originating from the spores of some plants. It is unclear whether it will still grow from its current form.

41449.Name: Kepari
41449.Description: Kepari are not related with the Kepa, and are instead akin to animals.

41450.Name: Kodomor
41450.Description: Since the disappearance of the goddesses, one of the most bizarre change is that these water-dwelling creatures are now active on land.

41451.Name: Kowak
41451.Description: It still tends to gravitate toward rotten flesh.

45090.Name: boss_Abomination
45090.Description: At first, they were created accidentally through the abuse of magic, but later malicious wizards and demons started creating them intentionally.

47306.Name: Lemur
47306.Description: It hasn't been discovered yet from which inanimate being this monster tranformed from.

47307.Name: Lemuria
47307.Description: Similar to the Lemur, but cold-resistant.

47308.Name: Hogma Fighter
47308.Description: While they look like guardsmen, these Hogmas have extensive battle experience.

47309.Name: Hogma_guard
47309.Description: Compared to an average Hogmas, they are very stronger, but their intelligence is lower.

47313.Name: Hydra
47313.Description: It was rare that Hydra encounter with humans before Medzio Diena, but whenever they were encountered, they were really hard to fight against. However, its immortality has disappeared so you would be able to kill it if you are competent enough.

47316.Name: boss_Clymen
47316.Description: It likes to hide in dark places or deep forests. It is timid so it only appears and attacks when it thinks the opponent is weak.

47317.Name: boss_Reaverpede
47317.Description: When it succeeds in suppressing an opponent, it has the tendency to paralyze the opponent and suck the body fluid of the opponent at a slow pace. After it increases its size, it attacks small-sized opponents to relieve its aggression and not to fulfill its hunger.

47318.Name: Colimencia
47318.Description: Initially, many people underestimated Colimencia, a strong Plant-type monster, since it was in a state of inactivity, but they received severe damage.

47319.Name: Jack O'Lantern
47319.Description: It is not well known since it didn't interact many times with humans, but this demon has both the cruelity and sense of humor.

47320.Name: Mothstem
47320.Description: It is fortunate that there aren't many cases that the host became a monster, but it's a difficult phenomenon to understand.

47321.Name: Harpeia
47321.Description: Though it is a legend that cannot be confirmed, but Harpeia used to follow Goddess Laima instead of the demons.

47323.Name: Moldyhorn
47323.Description: Humans and monsters have the tendency to harass others that are weaker than them.

47324.Name: Manticen
47324.Description: The demons are trying to give Manticen a great power so it can control other Insect-type monsters.

47325.Name: Moyabruka
47325.Description: The seeds that dropped from leaf molds combined with larvas and turned into monsters. Of course, they weren't discovered before Medzio Diena.

47326.Name: boss_Velorchard
47326.Description: They are the demons who took care of the garden of high-ranked demons and fruit trees. After Giltine decided to fight against the goddesses, they now participate in battles. Like most other demons, what they do and their battle skills and all are unrelated.

47327.Name: Zinute
47327.Description: It is a monster that is formed by binding an animal with a mineral. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.

47328.Name: Lauzinute
47328.Description: It is one of several variations of Zinute.

47329.Name: chupacabra_desert
47329.Description: Chupacabras appear simultaneously in various places and are threatening many lives and crops.

47347.Name: varv
47347.Description: Although small, it has grown bigger than its original state and hunts for meat throughout its life

47394.Name: arma
47394.Description: While it has no eyes, Arma has a highly developed sense of hearing and smell.

47395.Name: dimmer
47395.Description: It attacks people with the bead that it is holding every day.

47396.Name: flask
47396.Description: A monster variant that comes from a wizard's belongings. It is resistive to its original use.

47397.Name: flight_hope
47397.Description: A sad monster that can't fly.

47398.Name: tower_of_firepuppet
47398.Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.

47401.Name: wizards_marmotte
47401.Description: When the demons captured the Mage Tower, this doll was greatly affected. In particular, it instinctively hates magic users.

47402.Name: Experimental Slime
47402.Description: The slime is an organism in the demon realm. Its population exploded after the time when the plant Geant, especially around the Mage Tower.

47410.Name: Red Old Hook
47410.Description: One of the demon's lower level creature.They possess a little bit of intelligence.

47442.Name: Raflower
47442.Description: When botanists first discovered the Raflower, they planned on naming it Tripede, a name that has since been given to another monster.

47461.Name: Chromadog
47461.Description: A monster whose habitat has been relocated close to the volcano.

47462.Name: Rambear
47462.Description: It is a monster that has the power of various animals, so it is hard to face against.

47463.Name: Ultanun
47463.Description: Ultanuns have always been flightless birds even before its deformation.

47464.Name: Rubabos
47464.Description: Don't let its cute appearance fool you. This monster will try to tear you apart, given the chance.

47466.Name: Panto Shaman
47466.Description: The Panto Shaman is powerful, but it does not know were they are in a developing type of wizard. The obvious point is that you must pay more attention to them during combat.

47470.Name: Moyabu
47470.Description: Moyabu has evolved from the Moya. It is more violent than the Moya.

47471.Name: Bavon
47471.Description: When it comes to flight, Bavon would be better just floating there as is.

47472.Name: Tanu
47472.Description: A carnivorous plant that uses bait to catch food. It shred its food into pieces before swallowing.

47473.Name: Zignuts
47473.Description: A three headed monster. It is hard to tell whether the main body is just one head or all three.

47474.Name: Blue Panto Warrior
47474.Description: Pantos used to live at the Geli region from a long time ago and they kept their friendly relationship with humans before they were influenced on Medzio Diena.

47477.Name: Moglan
47477.Description: This beast that once exclusively roamed in the demon realm. Nowadays it is found all over the world, endangering other wildlife and humans.

47478.Name: Denden
47478.Description: The demons have tamed Denden and uses it for their means.

47479.Name: Doyor
47479.Description: If a moving poisonous mushroom makes you anxious, consider Doyor as an example.

47480.Name: Tipio
47480.Description: The yellow grass on its body looks supple. But if you touch it, it can be quite painful .

47482.Name: Terra Imp
47482.Description: The Terra Imp is quite mischievous. One should be aware of their belongings, as they might steal them.

47486.Name: Caro
47486.Description: Although it appears to have no sharp edges, it will when engaged in battle.

47488.Name: Leafnut
47488.Description: There are not too many cases of a fruit deformed monsters. Leafnut belongs to these few cases.

47497.Name: Unicorn
47497.Description: The Divine Tree which was the rest place for the goddesses became an enemy

47498.Name: Dullahan
47498.Description: Dullahan was one of the ghosts that was known to the human world and there were some kinds among them that do not harm people that are not related to the resentment. But, as you know, Medzio Diena changed everything.

47499.Name: boss_nuodai
47499.Description: This cruel lord of the flowers tries to control all lives in the region he controls regardless whether they are animals or plants.

47500.Name: Centaurus
47500.Description: Among the spirits of the forest, it is sad that the ones who were most close to the humans became the enemies of the humans.

47502.Name: Mallet Wyvern
47502.Description: It is known that the tail is used when they compete against each other, but you should not just rely on such tendency.

47503.Name: Turtai
47503.Description: Turtai is not on the same side with any goddess. Turtai always wants to strive for its benefits and to accomplish that, it betrays its own species or its allies. But, since there's nothing that humans can provide, there is no way that they would cooperate with humans.

47504.Name: Canceril
47504.Description: The transformation of the Canceril is now even considered ordinary in the world full of monsters derived from all sorts of lifeforms.

47505.Name: Crabil
47505.Description: The change like this looks normal in the world with many transformations of animals and plants have taken place.

47508.Name: Glackuman
47508.Description: Glackuman who dreams to become a famous fighter is only satisfied if he is dispatched to locations where a lot of fights are taking place.

47509.Name: Belian
47509.Description: Belian is not the type of monster that transformed from a plant, but rather, it is in a cursed state since it cannot complete the orders it received from the Demon King.

47510.Name: Merge
47510.Description: The monster which was transformed by demons after combining diverse types of creatures still shows its loyalty to the demons.

47511.Name: Plokste
47511.Description: It is a creature that places its origin to the demon realm. It is a kind that is related to Velnewt.

47512.Name: boss_woodhoungan
47512.Description: They can be called the Bokors of the demon realm. It is possible that they interact with Giltine and use the authority.

47513.Name: Velnewt
47513.Description: Velnewts usually group together and hunt together at the demon realm. But, they think that they are strong enough to act alone in our world so they tend to act individually.

47514.Name: boss_Blud
47514.Description: There's nothing special about the Demon Lord Blut. But, what is significant about him is that he is the Demon Lord that was randomly picked by Giltine in order to disturb the forecast of Laima.

47515.Name: boss_Neop
47515.Description: Neop was recently promoted as a Demon Lord by Giltine in order to disturb Laima's plans. Because of the promotion, he tries hard to learn more.

47528.Name: Mallardu
47528.Description: The flowers around its neck are actually real flowers rather than decorations.

47529.Name: Mali
47529.Description: If you carelessly touch the leaves on its head, Mali will unleash its relentless anger towards you.

47530.Name: Grummer
47530.Description: Be aware of the smoke that this creature spurts as it is highly toxic and will last for a while.

47531.Name: Hummingbird
47531.Description: A bite from its sharp beak causes persistent pain, which may last for a while.

47532.Name: Leafly
47532.Description: The edges of its wings are covered in poison. Touching it may cause paralysis.

57010.Name: wolf_statue_mage
57010.Description: A low-ranking demon who is always looking for opportunities to promote itself.

57015.Name: Nepenthes
57015.Description: Prior to Medzio Diena, the monster spent most of the time with sleeping so it wasn't that dangerous.

57016.Name: Seedmia
57016.Description: The Seedmia are very troublesome as they are able to shoot seeds over exceptionally long distances.

57017.Name: Firent
57017.Description: A moving tree monster that appeared after the Great Plant Cataclysm, it was named after its discoverer.

57018.Name: Galok
57018.Description: Galok is a monster who command workers in the demon realm.

57019.Name: Upent
57019.Description: Upent rapidly appeared from what once were flora with magical powers.

57021.Name: Glizardon
57021.Description: When the demons found glizardons, they immediately subjugated them into minions. Glizardons that aren't minions are still dangerous to humans.

57022.Name: Corylus
57022.Description: The Corylus is a mutant hybrid between plants, animals and minerals.

57023.Name: Red Luxodon
57023.Description: The reduction in size isn't the only thing that got better after this beast mutated.

57025.Name: Mantiwood
57025.Description: A mutated mantis. It has gotten stronger and has developed the ability to camouflage.

57027.Name: Beetow
57027.Description: After mutating, Beetow has developed an unreasonable and venomous nature. Its aggression has also become more significant.

57028.Name: Pawndel
57028.Description: Sister of Pawnd. It carries a sickle larger than its own body.

57029.Name: Carcashu
57029.Description: Carcashu is a fungus. Its toxins are strong, but there are parts of it that can be eaten.

57030.Name: Zibu_Maize
57030.Description: The Black Maize looks deceptively delicious, eating one will certainly poison you.

57031.Name: Merregina
57031.Description: Merregina is still under the control of Goddess Jurate, but since the goddesses are not intervening in human matters, it acts individually.

57033.Name: Velwriggler
57033.Description: This monster was bred by the demons and is known for its poisonous abilities.

57034.Name: Lapasape
57034.Description: Please don't assume that Lapasape can only be encountered in the deep forest, as it sometimes prowl outside to eat human crops.

57035.Name: duckey
57035.Description: Its appearance did not change much, but its physicality has. Lives near water.

57036.Name: Cronewt
57036.Description: This monster was once the size of a little finger, but it has since grown greatly.

57037.Name: Infro Hoglan
57037.Description: There are many birds that cannot fly after they've transformed to monsters.

57038.Name: Dumaro
57038.Description: The Dumaro is a newly discovered monster, which developed its toxic abilities after the Great Plant Cataclysm.

57039.Name: Lichenclops
57039.Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.

57040.Name: rubblem
57040.Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.

57042.Name: blindlem
57042.Description: It is a monster that was transformed from the plants that grew from stones which the humans threw away after refining them on Medzio Diena.

57043.Name: fallenlem
57043.Description: There is a variety of demonic soldiers in the demon realm. Their positions and ranks are not well known. The first record of Fallenlem came out from Agailla Flurry's biography.

57044.Name: Infro Blood
57044.Description: Infroblood is a case where plant spores transform into monsters. It can float.

57045.Name: ticen
57045.Description: Ticen wanders around with a spear, it tends to group with other Ticen variants.

57046.Name: tucen
57046.Description: A tip of Tucen's tail is made out of minerals.

57047.Name: Colimen
57047.Description: Among Plant-type monsters, exceptionally, they show tribunal characteristics. In an academic point of view, many people wonder whether they would possess more sociality.

57048.Name: colitile
57048.Description: They consume either small animals or insects. Nevertheless, they show hostility to the animals that are bigger than them, so anyone who encounters with them should be careful.

57049.Name: colistump
57049.Description: Since it retains its memory before deformation, this monster has grudges against the people who felled it.

57050.Name: Minivern
57050.Description: Although they are small, they are already hosts. Of course, they will keep growing.

57051.Name: belegg
57051.Description: It is uncertain which roles Belegg is responsible for and whether they are just moving magical creatures.

57052.Name: woodfung
57052.Description: The Woodfung is closely related to witchcraft.

57053.Name: Red Infrorocktor
57053.Description: They exhibit a unique hull that is a mix between stone and iron.

57055.Name: boss_gesti
57055.Description: Gesti is the Demon Queen among the other two Demon Kings who are all under Giltine's control, she is the only female. Under Gesti's control, many Demon Lords are following her instructions to attack humans.

57151.Name: Simorph
57151.Description: Simorph was reported as the first case that obtained the status of a demon as a monster due to its cooperation. Some masters don't want this to be the example of future unpleasant outcomes.

57202.Name: Siaumire
57202.Description: It is certain that Siaulamb is a species that existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that it wasn't discovered by humans within the thousand years of the kingdom history. And when the strange things occurred, they too apppeared under that influence and unfortunately they are against the humans.

57208.Name: Siaulav
57208.Description: It is certain that they existed before Medzio Diena. However, it is strange that they were never discovered by humans in the 1,000 years of the kingdom's history. And when strange things occured in the world after Medzio Diena, they appeared as a result of the influences and unfortunately they are against the humans.

57210.Name: Capria
57210.Description: Since the Pantos turned their backs on humans, the species that were never seen before appeared. Maybe... the demons are the culprit.

57213.Name: pawnd
57213.Description: A soldier that makes up the army of the demons.

57217.Name: Pendinmire
57217.Description: There's no one who wants to see the true nature of the hidden face behind this mask.

57250.Name: Abysmal Rodelin
57250.Description: It has been said that Helgasercle was made by the servants of the demon realm's aristocrats.

57252.Name: Hard Golemlet
57252.Description: The phenomena of the Golemlet absorbing the energy from Tree Root Crystals to become stronger occurs sometimes.

57269.Name: zombiegirl2
57269.Description: Deadborns turn into Rodelins when they receive a lot of influences from demons or when they are acknowledged by the high-ranked demons.

57275.Name: Cafrisun
57275.Description: Even when the Pantos were having a close relationship with humans, they actually weren't that friendly to humans. But, they weren't as hostile as they are now.

57311.Name: Riteris
57311.Description: There's a legend were Riteris was one of the masters in the past. Among the masters that are not wizards, some make contracts with the demons for immortality and look for others who are similar to them, then lead them to the demon realm.

57363.Name: Brown Sakmoli
57363.Description: They won't fall even if you attack them on their legs.

57374.Name: Gargoyle
57374.Description: A common misunderstanding of humans is that they think that the Dievdirbys were created by a mistake. Of course, we all know that is just silly and untrue.

57379.Name: Onion_Red_elite
57379.Description: Sometimes, people want to consume Kepas, but I want you to stop them.

57397.Name: Black Colifly
57397.Description: Colliflies have not awakened themselves as a species and even when they are going through the formation of a social group, demons nor humans are not using them. However, they are indeed threatening individually.

57402.Name: Keposeed
57402.Description: The difference between Kepos and Keposeeds is whether they are the hosts or the fluids. When you think about it, the difference between the hosts and the fluids might seem big, but except for the breeding ability, fluids are equally dangerous.

57403.Name: Lomor
57403.Description: If the monsters that base their origins on plants have an ability to create their offsprings, insides are often not filled.

57412.Name: Demon Lord Nuaele
57412.Description: Nuaele is one of those low-ranked Demon Lords. Strangely enough many demons follow it so that other Demon Lords do not treat them lightly.

57413.Name: Rumbufus
57413.Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.

57415.Name: Yeti
57415.Description: Yeti was just a legend prior to Medzio Diena and it's appearance was discovered only recently which led to it's acknowledgment as a monster.

57424.Name: Marionette
57424.Description: Marionette is a monster that looks familiar, but brings fear from that familiarity.

57425.Name: Fire Lord
57425.Description: This monster who betrayed Goddess Gabija can be called the heretic of the spirits.

57427.Name: Velmoski
57427.Description: It is a demons' pest that came to our world from the demon realm. They are disgusting creatures among us demons as well.

57428.Name: Veliamonkey
57428.Description: You shouldn't just think of it as a beast of the demons. This monster is actually intelligent!

57429.Name: Silva Griffin
57429.Description: A long time ago, there were times that they were tamed and mounted by humans.

57444.Name: Glutton
57444.Description: This monster is the creation of the Demon Lord Naktis who almost reaches the level of an actual Demon Lord.

57445.Name: Succubus
57445.Description: Succubus is obtains her commands from the Demon Lord Naktis, but she isn't optimistic about Naktis.

57447.Name: Rabbee
57447.Description: It is sad that we cannot see animals like Rabbees in their appearances from the past.

57448.Name: eldigo
57448.Description: Eldigo listens to the orders of stronger monsters in order to survive. But, the opponents it faces are usually stronger so it often gets sacrificed.

57449.Name: Socket
57449.Description: Sockets used to live deep inside our world and in the demon realm. They believe on Giltine's promise that their territory will be guaranteed in the earth.

57450.Name: Honeybean
57450.Description: Austeya goddess was upset that the insects which she controls transformed, and she was especially upset after looking at this monster's trasformed appearance. This monster is one of the reasons that Austeya goddess is very firm against the demons after Medzio Diena.

57456.Name: Vasilisk
57456.Description: This was a monster that threatened the human society a long time ago. When Roxona turned into a petrified city, there was a rumor that there was a herd of Vasilisks.

57459.Name: Pink Root Mole
57459.Description: It would be great if they still look for food on the ground, but these beasts nowadays are not the type of animals that we used to know.

57463.Name: Mine Predator
57463.Description: Goblins that used to live in certain areas for a long time enhance their attack abilities and adaptability.

57467.Name: Melatinun
57467.Description: Some scholars want to know how grown up Melatinuns are like. But, adventurers, masters and soldiers don't want to know about them and they don't want to see their appearances.

57473.Name: FD_whip_vine_purple
57473.Description: Some plant scholars wanted to name Tripedes to the moving Raflowers when were discovered, but that name was given to another monster as we now known as the Raflower.

57475.Name: FD_Deadbornscab
57475.Description: There are some instances Deadborns was born from the shells the Deadborns molted out or from the parts that were seperated from the bodies due to injuries. The original Deadborns had the tendency to discriminate these newcomers and humans also distinguish them from the original ones.

57488.Name: Ashrong
57488.Description: Which part is the main part from Ashrong's body? Although, it may not be a helpful information to battles, this may be interested for some people.

57489.Name: Cornuts
57489.Description: Which part is the main part from Cornuts' body? Although, it may not be a helpful information in battles, this may be interested for some people.

57490.Name: Papayam
57490.Description: Which part is the main part from Papayam's body? Although, it may not be a helpful information in battles, this may be interested for some people.

57491.Name: Terapede
57491.Description: This monster was named like this not due to the number of legs it has, but it's order in the research list.

57492.Name: Triffid
57492.Description: This monster obtained it's legendary name due to it's appearance. Other than that, this monster doesn't have anything special.

57493.Name: Crocoman
57493.Description: This monster possesses scary fist power and tenacious aggressiveness. It's specialty of hiding well in other places has totally disappeared.

57510.Name: Outer World Large Panto Spearman
57510.Description: Pantos used to live in Gele region for a long time and before it was influnced on Medzio Diena, it kept it's close relationship with humans. Even if the Panto is totally different from normal Pantos, they originated from our world.

57525.Name: digo
57525.Description: It's hard for humans to look at it, but Digo likes to race with other species or monsters.

57544.Name: Nuaele
57544.Description: Nuaele belongs to a low level position. But, unexpectedly, many demons are following it so other demon lords don't treat it lightly.

57570.Name: Panto Pathfinder
57570.Description: Its elongated pupils are a distinctive feature.

57573.Name: Npanto_staff
57573.Description: A Panto variant with distinctively high intelligence. They often show up with the other Panto variants.

57574.Name: Npanto_sword
57574.Description: A Panto with excellent fighting skills and is one of the strongest subspecies in the forest.

57584.Name: Dionys
57584.Description: Dionis, the guardian tree of Goddess Vakarine has been accompanied with Vakarine since when she was born. That is why Dionis is always besides the statue of Goddess Vakarine. You can also see them at teleport statues that enable teleportation between different regions.

57592.Name: Karas_mage
57592.Description: In substance, this is the kind of Golem and it is a creature that possesses the wish of the creator, magical power and the ego.

57596.Name: Templeslave_sword
57596.Description: Like Temple Shooters, they strive hard to reach for a higher status in the Goblin society.

57628.Name: Saltisdaughter Magician
57628.Description: Saltistters live in cold, rugged areas so their amount hardly increases. The instances where they appear in diverse transformations like Saltisdaughter are of course, after Medzio Diena.

57632.Name: Goblin Wizard
57632.Description: After Medzio Diena, as the environment turned favorable to the Goblins, their number increased and they wanted to invade the land of the humans. For your reference, Woodgoblins and goblins are not directly related.

57648.Name: Ticen Magician
57648.Description: By looking at the spear Ticen is carrrying, the assumption that there may be other kinds of Ticens out there turned out to be true and many kinds of Ticens were created and they are moving in a herd. They care about sociality.

57653.Name: Infrogalas Mage
57653.Description: It is certain that Infrogalas is close to Gaigalas, but we haven't yet actually identified the origin of Gaigalas at the moment so it's origin and the birth are still unknown. However, it is fortunate that other information that is needed when fighting against it is known.

57660.Name: Woodluwa
57660.Description: A monster that the sorcerers of the devil realm called out using noir. There's a rumor that they use the spirits in the forest after capturing them, but that has yet to be confirmed.

57661.Name: Glyphring
57661.Description: It is not uncommon that the stone statues that are engraved with magical power or parts of architectures move to harm humans. After Medzio Diena, there's no one who think that could be a bit strange.

57665.Name: Pumpleflap
57665.Description: Until the year after Medzio Diena, people thought that the monsters that turned from the crops that haven't been harvested would not appear again if harvesters were careful. However, they lost their hope when the monsters started growing by themselves. Pumpleflap is an example of this.

57668.Name: Rudasjack
57668.Description: Some places in the devil realm are filled with these floating objects in the sky.

57669.Name: Jukotail
57669.Description: Jukotail doesn't walk on it's tail. It is floating in the air and it's insides is empty. But, we don't know if their insides are emptied within a short period of time after it's death.

57670.Name: Pyran
57670.Description: Pyran is created when the egg of a reptile that is in ashes transforms and hatches.

57672.Name: Velfiggy
57672.Description: A tool that is used by sorcerer of demons. When the ritual is over, the sorcerer would obtain the ego.

57673.Name: Burialer
57673.Description: A monster that is being created when the tombstone of the dead and the spirit of the grave combine inaccurately.

57676.Name: Velaphid
57676.Description: A monster that is being created when a part of the transformed monster from an arthropod gets transformed independently.

57677.Name: anchor
57677.Description: Many things were transformed into monsters since Medzio Diena. It is frightening to think about the whereabouts of many anchors the humans dropped into the sea. I just hope that Goddess Jurate keep them tied to the sea.

57679.Name: Pendrosium
57679.Description: After it became a monster, it was known that it had many uses, so they are being hunted by humans. There's a rumor that the Winterspoon family buys them for a good price.

57680.Name: VelStool
57680.Description: It is hard to distinguish them from other monsters that are transformed from other mushroom types, but they are definitely the ones that are transformed from the creatures of the devil realm.

57681.Name: Malstatue
57681.Description: In various regions, they created either the Kupoles or the idols of the spirits. Some of them started to work as evil creatures after Medzio Diena.

57682.Name: Stonacon
57682.Description: Stonacons are originated from the plant seeds which chipmunk type monsters forgot after buring them under the ground.

57684.Name: Glyquare
57684.Description: They are the monsters that were created from the transformations of stone architectures that were engraved with the letters of magic or runes.

57686.Name: Sowpent
57686.Description: It is still to be investigated how the monsters that were created from the seeds of the plants have the appearance of snake.

57688.Name: Elet
57688.Description: A long time ago, Elet used to be a fairy or a soul. They received the curse of Goddess Ausrine and they hid into the human world and lived on. Since Medzio Diena, when the demons invaded the world, they are showing their determination to participate with the other demons.

57689.Name: Nuo
57689.Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons.

57690.Name: Nuka
57690.Description: Nuka is under the control of the Demon King Vaiga and was dispatched here to fulfill the tasks that Gesti received from Giltine. But, Gesti is controlling them unlike what Vaiga once thought.

57691.Name: Elma
57691.Description: Elma is one of Gesti's bodyguards, she is dispatched to various duties and also works as a guard at the devil realm.

57692.Name: defender_spider
57692.Description: It gets created when the stone pieces or the stone figures of the buildings which the demons stayed change.

57707.Name: Mandara
57707.Description: He has four strong arms. If you don't be careful, you may receive major damage.

57714.Name: Harugal
57714.Description: A demon that follows the Demon Lord Hauberk. Most of them still show their loyalty to Hauberk even after their owner was sealed by Helgasercle.

57715.Name: Hohen Mane
57715.Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantegeous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future.

57726.Name: Grim Reaper
57726.Description: Unlike other specter type monsters, Reapers used to work for quite some time in the demon realm and it's evil whereabouts are recorded in the kingdom's history.

57827.Name: boss_hauberk
57827.Description: Demon Lord Hauberk signed a secret treaty with Agailla Flurry, who is known as one of the greatest mages in the history, but after that treaty had been discovered by Demon Lord Helgasercle, the body of Hauberk was ripped into pieces and those pieces were sealed away and scattered across the world. Nevertheless, Hauberk still influences his servants and dreams of his resurrection and return.

57844.Name: Lapemiter
57844.Description: Lapemiter is a unique occupation that is highly respected, but is also looked down upon among Lapes. A Lapemiter serves a religious role, but the other Lapes don't put great emphasis on religious rituals, so they want a Lapemiter to do their exhausting duty.

57845.Name: Lapezard
57845.Description: Unlike the prejudice of the humans, Lapezards are not Lapes that obtained their current status through long training. Most of them are selected by their breeds and they grow up accordingly and receive the necessary food to become a Lapezard.

57846.Name: Lapfighter
57846.Description: Their status is not high among Lapes, but they are most dangerous and they get encountered often. To receive respect from the other Lapes, they act violently to the ones they encounter with.

57847.Name: Lapflammer
57847.Description: For a Lape to Lapflammer, they just need to obtain the weapons they need. But its not that easy since when Lapflammers die, the weapons also get destroyed so its not that easy for the Lapes.

57848.Name: Ferret Archer
57848.Description: Ferret Archers usually engages in battles, but they sometimes shoot down the fruits on tall trees. It's not that other ferrets asked them to do it, but they just do that for fun when they are not engaged in battles.

57849.Name: Ferret Merchant
57849.Description: They sometimes move the objects, but they usually share the processed fruit products to other ferrets. It is unknown whether they receive any rewards for that or they are responsible to do so.

57850.Name: ferret_folk
57850.Description: They look small, but they are matured ferrets. They sometimes become other ferrets depending on the properties of the breeds and the environment that they live in.

57851.Name: Ferret Loader
57851.Description: This ferret does not possess any distinct characteristic. But due to long labor, they possess strong power, so you should not underestimate it.

57852.Name: Ferret Empty Porter
57852.Description: They do work while supervising the works of other ferrets.

57853.Name: Ferret Searcher
57853.Description: This ferret is responsible for looking for other enemies and useful fruits.

57854.Name: Ferret Slinger
57854.Description: Like Ferret Archers, they either attack enemies or shoot down the fruits. One advantage they have over archers is that they sometimes use hard fruits as bullets.

57855.Name: Ferret Supply Soldier
57855.Description: This ferret has an inferior status compared to the other ferrets. This ferret helps with the works of other ferrets and they also participate in battles.

57856.Name: Lapeman
57856.Description: It is not assured that the Lapeman is the undead of a Lape. However, the Lapeman mostly receives respect from the other Lapes.

57866.Name: Rafene
57866.Description: We can tell Lape society is gradually becoming more complex and differentiated by looking at them distinguishing themselves from each other for even slight differences between them. When humans see them, they look the same, but they differentiate themselves from each other by having different names so humans also call them differently.

58014.Name: Sword Pell Master
58014.Description: This is the target for practitioners' practice

58017.Name: Gosaru
58017.Description: Many people are guessing that it is a monster that transformed from a hedgehog, but it's origin hasn't been discovered yet.

58018.Name: Parrot
58018.Description: We are not sure about the uses of the thorns that are on the back. There are many cases that transformed monsters keep their appearances before transformations even if they don't have any functions, but sometimes their functions get discovered later so scholars are not making any decisions yet.

58019.Name: Polibu
58019.Description: Polibu eats small animals or insects and they even eats dead bodies. But, they attack humans to have just one bite so you should be cautious.

58020.Name: Ponpon
58020.Description: There are many cases that some parts of the plants become monsters. For Ponpons, the fruits had transformed.

58021.Name: Canchobird
58021.Description: Even if I don't explain to you, you would understand that it would hurt a lot when you get attacked by thick beaks.

58038.Name: Prison Cutter
58038.Description: Violence and cruelty is normal in this place so it's a perfect place for demons. They enjoyed tortures and killings in the demon realm.

58050.Name: Summoned Gray Chupacabra
58050.Description: Chupacabras move quite stealthily. That being said, it's much more dangerous for humans if there are elite Chupacabras.

58071.Name: boss_Marnoks
58071.Description: Giltine thought that Demon Queen Gesti was not working as expected as she dispatched the many Demon Lords recently. Marnox is a recent typical Demon Lord.

58072.Name: Pag Ampler
58072.Description: Pag members belong to the high class among other demons. The other demon also feels fear due to their cruelty. Pags only bully other demons who are not strong under the Demon King Kartas' guard, they appeared with the request by Giltine in this world.

58079.Name: Charog
58079.Description: A modified frog. It seems to see the original shape due to the hard modification.

58080.Name: Charcoal Walker
58080.Description: It's unsure that the demons ignore these monsters and use for the firewood by sacrificing.

58081.Name: Flamme
58081.Description: They had started to form a union when Gesti received the mission from Giltine to chase after the revelation. Since Medzio Diena, Flammes were created until then and their subspecies were dispatched to various places according to their creator, Gesti's order.

103007.Name: Blok Archer
103007.Description: Bloks just appeared within the last year, so there isn't much information about it yet.

103009.Name: Kenol
103009.Description: There are quite a few reckless people who are going after the monsters that have big ores like the Kenol attached onto the bodies of the monsters. It would have been better if they had acted more cautiously when thinking about the disaster that was brought to the world.

400002.Name: Large Kepa
400002.Description: There are people who try to eat the Large Kepa sometimes. Don't let them.

400003.Name: Onion_Red
400003.Description: Contrary to popular belief, it's the Red Kepas that are most similar to the original Kepa.

400021.Name: Haming
400021.Description: Despite its tough skin, the Hamming is a fairly feeble monster.

400041.Name: Bokchoy
400041.Description: Originally stalks of plants, the Chinency have since evolved to their current form.

400042.Name: Mutant Chinency
400042.Description: It has a poison like the Chinency. However, its poison has a lower effect than the Chinency.

400061.Name: Jukopus
400061.Description: Very little is known about the Jukopus' internal structure.

400063.Name: Gray Jukopus
400063.Description: Depending on its maturity, this monster may develop a variety of different combat techniques.

400083.Name: Blue Pokuborn
400083.Description: There are many things you should be aware of with this monster. Above all, don't get hit by its charge attack.

400084.Name: Green Pokuborn
400084.Description: Even after mutating, their meat is still edible.

400101.Name: banshee
400101.Description: The souls of those who ventured to the underworld now appear as demons.

400103.Name: Evil Spirit
400103.Description: A soul that did not receive the guidance of the goddess. It was born through demonic control.

400104.Name: Large Banshee
400104.Description: It is a demon form that the souls touched with Evil. The main different is that It has been corrupted to mix demon's soul not human's soul became evil.

400121.Name: Beehive
400121.Description: Goddess Austeja has been hard to look over the mission, after that, these monsters have been appeared beyond the goddess' power.

400141.Name: Bushspider
400141.Description: Crawling amongst the shadows of the forest, this monster has evolved greatly in size over time.

400161.Name: Disgusting Dionia
400161.Description: Dionia gained the strong spell by Demon Master Bramble. So, it seems originaly transformed to monsters from plants, but it maybe think belong to demons.

400162.Name: dionia_mini
400162.Description: Dionia is known for his wisdom is week, but he tends to show an affection for his spore only. It's quite strange situation considering the Plant-types.

400181.Name: Blue Fragaras
400181.Description: This monster grew bigger in size, but not much has changed.  In the past, this still used to be a deadly and vicious plant.

400209.Name: GoblinWarrior
400209.Description: It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained, or just have a natural aptitude for combat.

400241.Name: Meduja
400241.Description: Some people say a Meduja can be used to contact the souls of the dead.

400244.Name: Red Meduja
400244.Description: Researchers have asserted that plants have souls. The Meduja are the mutated form of such souls.

400261.Name: boss_ellaganos
400261.Description: Ellaganos is created with the strong power and form, after the unique undead which mixed with the dead and stone used at the grave over many years.

400281.Name: honey_bee
400281.Description: Some say they would rather choose to take an arrow than experience a bite by the Bite.

400302.Name: puragi_blue
400302.Description: Blue Puragis love to kill and pillage.

400303.Name: Green Puragi
400303.Description: No one has ever seen the face hidden behind its mask.

400323.Name: Black Zigri
400323.Description: A demon minion found throughout the world.

400341.Name: Fisherman
400341.Description: The reason why Fishermen are classified as monsters is due to their fishing rods controlling the creatures.

400344.Name: Fisherman_red
400344.Description: This fisherman's actions are often unexplainable.

400361.Name: Gribaru
400361.Description: Its head stem can be used for various purposes, such as releasing attractants and detecting hidden targets.

400377.Name: Thorn Forest Griba
400377.Description: There are famous comments by someone, this monster is hard to eat and to protect.

400381.Name: Matsum
400381.Description: Whether the Matsum originated from a plant, animal, or mineral is unimportant. What you should know is that its dangerous.

400401.Name: boss_mirtis
400401.Description: Mirtis is considered a low-ranked Demon Lord of all the others. The reason why is probably because she failed many missions that were given to her from Giltine. On her last mission, she was sealed by a human. Since Medzio Diena, she has now the freedom to catch up on her failed mission.

400402.Name: Mirtis Ego
400402.Description: There are some Demon Lords who create a clone of their own or divide their own powers. This is one of those cases. In addition, the Sorcerer gain advantages by using similar magic that the demons use.

400421.Name: boss_molich
400421.Description: Molich achieved lots of success by served many Demon Lords over many years, and he has a chance to reach more higher rank lately. Scholars who know the demon history expected if that happened Molich will be pass the low rank Demon Lord like Bramble and Mirtis.

400443.Name: Red Griba
400443.Description: Although their bright color makes them pretty visible, it's still hard to evade their attacks.

400461.Name: mushroom_ent
400461.Description: This monster was once described as hard to block and hard to eat.

400462.Name: mushroom_ent_blue
400462.Description: A large, strong, tough monster and reluctant prey of hunters.

400481.Name: pappus_kepa
400481.Description: Kepa age quickly at the expense of their strength. Be careful of its pungent odor, which has gotten stronger with age.

400484.Name: Red Old Kepa
400484.Description: Its dilapidated color from aging only substantiates its danger.

400503.Name: Black Rafflesia
400503.Description: This plant's leaves are stronger than leather.

400504.Name: Red Rafflesia
400504.Description: This plant's leaf is more strong than leather. Especially, like old leaf is more strong.

400521.Name: Raffly
400521.Description: Raffly hunts small insects, even after transformed.

400542.Name: Blue Ridimed
400542.Description: Even though it mutated from a herb, its entire body is now made of solid wood.

400561.Name: Sakmoli
400561.Description: Attacking its legs will not cause it to topple over.

400562.Name: Green Sakmoli
400562.Description: Not fall down even attacking legs. But, there are no special ways.

400661.Name: boss_spector_gh
400661.Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.

400682.Name: Black Spectra
400682.Description: Unlike other wraith monsters, these monsters were often evil souls even when they were alive.

400685.Name: Green Rikaus
400685.Description: Ghost caused by demons has various form's features and color.

400721.Name: thornball
400721.Description: This floating seed has transmuted, losing its outer fluff for a solid shell and thorns. However, its ability to float has stayed intact.

400741.Name: Woodspirit
400741.Description: Each Woodspirit has various personalities. Unlike the outline color, there are various it such as solo play and demon's pawn. But, there are no Woodspirit which have a like to a human.

400761.Name: Woodman
400761.Description: The fact that the Woodsman can't move is a real blessing.

400762.Name: Blue Woodsman
400762.Description: It is so fortunate that Woodsman is not an active monster.

400781.Name: slime_dark
400781.Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.

400801.Name: schlesien_claw
400801.Description: These guardians were placed in many tombs, starting with the Royal Mausoleum of Zachariel the Great, to stop intruders. Its name came from grave robbers who've encountered them.

400821.Name: schlesien_darkmage
400821.Description: The Madakia were created by court wizards to fend off intruders that were more dangerous than grave robbers.

400841.Name: schlesien_guard
400841.Description: The Wheelen is one of many magical creations made to protect the sealed tombs that have no current overseer.

400861.Name: schlesien_heavycavarly
400861.Description: The stone cavalry of the Royal Mausoleum are magical creations made to withstand even the most heavily-armed of knights.

400901.Name: boss_bramble
400901.Description: Bramble is not utmost smart among the other Demon Lords. However, Gesti likes his personality and provides him with a lot of power. According to a story, Bramble tried to steal the goddess' relic where other Demon Lords have failed in.

400921.Name: treemonster
400921.Description: According to the story, the willow which got the unique disease at Medzio Diena has been changed to like this form plant.

400941.Name: Hanaming
400941.Description: Leaves fallen from a dead Hanaming wither rapidly.

400964.Name: Chupacabra_Gray_Elite
400964.Description: Chupacabras move quite stealthily. That being said, it's much more dangerous for humans if there are elite Chupacabras.

400981.Name: Popolion_Blue
400981.Description: A Popolion's voice is said to break even glass bottles.

401001.Name: Sauga_s
401001.Description: The different thing between the normal Golem is that they follow the regular rules. Even current people could not understand it.

401021.Name: Scorpion
401021.Description: Since Medzio Diena, many variation monsters have appeared, but it is not sure that whether Golem types made by magic or vairation of an organism.

401041.Name: Tontulia
401041.Description: The Tontulia is a more mobile mutation of the Tontus.

401061.Name: Tontus
401061.Description: As cacti mutated into Tontus, the lives of the residents in desert enviroment worsened.

401081.Name: Beetle
401081.Description: Compared to other animal species, Vekarabe didn't change much from their original form when they turned into monsters. However, their aggresion definitely a new addition.

401121.Name: Moving_trap
401121.Description: The Boowook are one of the many defensive systems left by Zachariel the Great in the Royal Mausoleum.

401141.Name: boss_bearkaras
401141.Description: Some of the monsters have strong powers by changing the format at Medzio Diena tried to make a cooperation with Demon or hired by them.

401201.Name: Helmet Bug
401201.Description: Monsters that have simply grown in size and aggressiveness are a sight for sore eyes, at least when compared to some of the other terrors in this world.

401221.Name: Coliflower
401221.Description: Though this stationary monster isn't especially hostile towards humans, it still attacks all warm-blooded animals.

401222.Name: Coliflowerr
401222.Description: This monster is not especially hostile towards humans but attacks all all warm-blooded animals.

401241.Name: Wolf_statue
401241.Description: Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since shifted into a state that attacks anyone who enters.

401261.Name: Cockatries
401261.Description: While the normal Cockatrice is fairly small, its terrifying breath and glance can petrify its foes instantly.

401281.Name: Tombdog
401281.Description: Unlike the feature, this monster only appears under complex conditions and special circumstance.

401301.Name: zinutekas
401301.Description: Though their appearance can be mistaken with other similar-looking monsters, Zinutekas are artificially constructed by magic.

401341.Name: Pokubu
401341.Description: Despite its appearance, the Pokubu can be quite ferocious.

401364.Name: Zinute_Big
401364.Description: It is a monster that is formed by binding an aninal with minenal. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.

401401.Name: Dandel
401401.Description: What is more frightening than a Dandel's soft, keratinized hair is its vitality and aggressiveness.

401421.Name: Candlespider
401421.Description: There is no meaning of the question that candle to change monster or monster to change candle. Since Medzio Diena, many monsters appeared is target to kill not curiosity.

401441.Name: Corpse_Flower
401441.Description: This is not the result of a flower blooming from a dead body. It's a bit awkard to say it's a 'fruit'.

401461.Name: Flying_Flog
401461.Description: Due to its environment, this monster has come to have a variety of forms. This one has evolved to have wings.

401481.Name: Hepatica_green
401481.Description: It is not bad that the deformed monsters are like these numbers by considering the moss lives in the various temperate region.

401501.Name: Leaf_diving
401501.Description: Despite its appearance, these creatures are not hollow on the inside.

401541.Name: Salamion
401541.Description: Sorcerers changed these humans who were once a wizard after shown interest in the demon realm.

401601.Name: Gravegolem
401601.Description: Originally created with good intentions, the golem now lives possessed by evil energy.

401621.Name: Fire_Dragon
401621.Description: A lesser demon summoned by its demonic superiors to invade towers.

401622.Name: Fire_Dragon_green
401622.Description: These lesser demons come in countless types due to their populous numbers.

401623.Name: Fire_Dragon_purple
401623.Description: This species was once fairly rare; however, in recent times, their numbers have greatly increased.

401641.Name: Cockat
401641.Description: The Big Cockatrice is quite dangerous, as its glare and breath can petrify any opponent. Engaging this creature should not be taken lightly.

401661.Name: boss_Sequoia
401661.Description: It was created to protect humans by Dievdirbys Master, but it has been the harmful monsters to change the characteristtics.

401681.Name: Corrupted
401681.Description: Old Status that Goddess' divinity left from here will absorb the demons.

401701.Name: Bagworm
401701.Description: The number of Bagworms is no longer increasing, yet its current population is enough not to worry about extinction.

401702.Name: Bagworm_Big
401702.Description: This kind of monster won't be discovered anymore. But, the number of these monsters that currently exist seems to indicate that there is no worry about extinction.

401741.Name: Old Hook
401741.Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.

401761.Name: stub_tree
401761.Description: Even though there are less logging activities, the monsters that originated from the stumps continue to show up. They appear to be formed out of the residues of Plant-type monsters.

401801.Name: Root Mole
401801.Description: The eyesight is not bad unlike its name.

450221.Name: boss_Golem
450221.Description: Almost Golem in the world originally crafted for good purposes, but now, They have been working caused by the evil spirit.

4014210.Name: Poiming
4014210.Description: A subspecies of the Hanaming. Recently found and currently still in research.
